		<h1>Organization Setup I (3% )</h1>

		
		<p>Notes:</p>
<p><strong>Org setup</strong> - covers basic settings that need to be reviwed before implementation. Such as default TLC(Yimezone, language,currency). Alternate settings- SLA(data/file storage, license count, API usage).</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Company Settings - <strong>(TLC HILL SF)</strong></p>
<p>1. Locale - define format of date,time,name,address and number</p>
<p>2. TimeZone - define date and time format</p>
<p>3.Currency - single and multi-currency</p>
<p>4. Businees Hours and Holiday - escalation role and entitlement</p>
<p>5. Organization ID - uique, 15 characters</p>
<p>6. Language - 3 level support ,full sipport, end user and platform only support. Transaltion workbench for translation</p>
<p>7. Lincense - user lincense, total, used,remining</p>
<p>8. Storage - data and file </p>
<p>9. Fiscal year - standard (12 month cycle) and custom</p>
<p><strong>Default Locale</strong> - locale settings controls how different values are displayed within SF.</p>
<p>Locale - controls language and format of date and time, currency, address, name and number</p>
<p>Default settings on <strong>Company Information page</strong></p>
<p>User can change default locale settings managed on <strong>Language and Time Zone </strong>settings in <strong>user's personal settings</strong>.</p>
<p>Language Setup-</p>
<p>End user language- <span style="font-family: 'Salesforce Sans', Arial, sans-serif;font-size: 13px">end-user languages, Salesforce provides translated labels for all standard objects and pages, <strong>except admin pages, Setup, and Help. </strong></span><span style="font-family: 'Salesforce Sans', Arial, sans-serif;font-size: 13px">End-user languages are intended only for personal use by end users. Salesforce doesn’t provide customer support in end-user languages.</span></p>
<p>Platform-only - <span style="font-family: 'Salesforce Sans', Arial, sans-serif;font-size: 13px">In situations where Salesforce doesn’t provide default translations, use platform-only languages to localize apps and custom functionality that you build on the Salesforce Platform. You can translate items such as custom labels, custom objects, and field names. You can also rename most standard objects, labels, and fields. Informational text and non-field label text aren’t translatable.</span></p>
<p>Multi-currency:</p>
<p><span style="color: #3c3d3e;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 11.36px;font-weight: bold">Advanced Currency Management : </span><span style="color: #222222;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;font-size: 11.36px">Allows you to manage dated exchange rates that map a currency conversion rate to a specific date range</span></p>
